to keep secrets. Ethan.

265
00:19:29.335 --> 00:19:30.461
Fine.

266
00:19:30.545 --> 00:19:32.839
If you take me to the lake. I'll tell you.

267
00:20:46.371 --> 00:20:47.580
What are you doing out here?

268
00:20:48.539 --> 00:20:49.749
Saw you walk off alone.

269
00:20:49.832 --> 00:20:51.834
Thought you might be
doing something stupid.

270
00:20:51.918 --> 00:20:53.586
like going back to the ruins.

271
00:20:56.214 --> 00:20:57.298
Go away.

272
00:20:59.550 --> 00:21:00.593
Julie.

273
00:21:00.677 --> 00:21:02.637
I'm not going to the ruins. okay?

274
00:21:03.680 --> 00:21:05.848
I need to get something from our house.

275
00:21:05.932 --> 00:21:06.933
Okay.

276
00:21:07.976 --> 00:21:09.227
Our old house.

277
00:21:10.436 --> 00:21:11.938
The one that collapsed?

278
00:21:13.022 --> 00:21:14.482
No. No fucking way.

279
00:21:14.565 --> 00:21:16.401
I was inside that thing
when it came down. remember?

280
00:21:16.484 --> 00:21:17.610
-Okay.
-It's too unstable.

281
00:21:17.694 --> 00:21:18.695
Okay.

282
00:21:19.737 --> 00:21:22.240
No. look. look.
All right. stop. stop. stop.

283
00:21:23.533 --> 00:21:25.159
What's in there that's so important?

284
00:21:26.995 --> 00:21:30.373
I told you that thing that I can do.
My brother called it Storywalking.

285
00:21:31.124 --> 00:21:33.918
I learned about it from one of his books.
and all his books are under the house now.

286
00:21:34.002 --> 00:21:36.462
And I need to know
if there's anything in there

287
00:21:36.546 --> 00:21:38.715
about how to control it
so I can go back and save my dad

288
00:21:38.798 --> 00:21:39.882
without getting killed.

289
00:21:39.966 --> 00:21:42.760
And maybe that is stupid. okay?
But I'm not asking your permission.

290
00:21:42.844 --> 00:21:43.886
I'm going.

291
00:21:44.929 --> 00:21:47.181
So you can help me.
or you can leave me alone.

292
00:21:53.813 --> 00:21:55.106
Give me that.

293
00:22:15.334 --> 00:22:16.711
You still want that bullet?

294
00:22:18.963 --> 00:22:21.340
There's something I need you
to do for me first.

295
00:22:25.595 --> 00:22:27.847
-What's he doing?
-I think he's sleeping.

296
00:22:29.724 --> 00:22:30.725
Jade?

297
00:22:32.226 --> 00:22:33.269
What?

298
00:22:34.729 --> 00:22:36.606
-Let's go.
-We just got here.

299
00:22:38.775 --> 00:22:41.360
-It's not what I'm looking for.
-How do you know that?

300
00:22:42.278 --> 00:22:43.529
I just do.

301
00:22:45.073 --> 00:22:47.784
Ethan. you promisedâ€¦

302
00:22:48.785 --> 00:22:51.412
that if I brought you here.
you would tell me.

303
00:22:52.538 --> 00:22:54.332
I need to find the Lake of Tears.

304
00:22:55.333 --> 00:22:57.251
It's a lake with magical powers.

305
00:22:57.335 --> 00:22:59.378
What kind of magical powers?

306
00:22:59.462 --> 00:23:01.130
It can make people better
when they're hurt.

307
00:23:01.923 --> 00:23:03.299
I thought I made it up.

308
00:23:04.425 --> 00:23:06.594
But my dad told me it's here.

309
00:23:08.262 --> 00:23:09.555
I need to find it.

310
00:23:10.723 --> 00:23:12.183
When did he tell you that?

311
00:23:13.726 --> 00:23:16.687
Yesterdayâ€¦ out by the RV.

312
00:23:17.563 --> 00:23:20.316
Maybe once I find it.
it can make him better.

313
00:23:20.942 --> 00:23:22.318
Maybe he'll come back.

314
00:23:23.361 --> 00:23:24.695
Maybe Jade can help.

315
00:23:25.446 --> 00:23:26.447
Jade!

316
00:23:26.531 --> 00:23:28.533
Oh. for Christ's sakes. what?

317
00:23:28.616 --> 00:23:30.910
We need to find the Lake of Tears.

318
00:23:31.911 --> 00:23:33.246
The Lake of what?

319
00:23:34.205 --> 00:23:35.706
It's a kid's book. though. right?

320
00:23:36.332 --> 00:23:38.709
It's stories made up for little kids.

321
00:23:39.544 --> 00:23:41.879
Before we got here. I thought
monsters were made up. too.

322
00:23:43.714 --> 00:23:44.841
Fair point.

323
00:23:52.014 --> 00:23:53.057
You good?

324
00:23:54.100 --> 00:23:57.186
This is where I talked to my dad
the day the house collapsed.

325
00:24:02.024 --> 00:24:04.610
He was still down there
when the sun was setting.

326
00:24:07.113 --> 00:24:10.074
I was so scared that we were just
going to lose him right then and there.

327
00:24:17.373 --> 00:24:19.792
He kept telling me
everything was going to be okay.

328
00:24:21.502 --> 00:24:23.129
that I shouldn't be afraid.

329
00:24:24.338 --> 00:24:25.339
Heyâ€¦

330
00:24:27.049 --> 00:24:28.384
Why don't you let me do this?

331
00:24:28.467 --> 00:24:29.760
What?

332
00:24:29.844 --> 00:24:31.554
I can handle a couple of books.

333
00:24:32.597 --> 00:24:36.475
Besides. someone's gonna need to be
up here if something happens. right?

334
00:24:39.145 --> 00:24:41.189
No. No. I should be theâ€¦

335
00:24:41.314 --> 00:24:43.399
-It's my thing. I should be the one--
-Hey. hey. hey.

336
00:24:43.482 --> 00:24:44.525
Storywalker.

337
00:24:45.776 --> 00:24:48.654
Why don't you let someone else
do the cool shit for change. huh?

338
00:24:50.072 --> 00:24:51.532
It's good for my self-esteem.

339
00:24:58.497 --> 00:25:00.583
There's a--
There's a way in over here.

340
00:25:06.923 --> 00:25:10.009
In the story. Achan caused
the whole nation of Israel to suffer

341
00:25:10.092 --> 00:25:11.802
because he offended God.

342
00:25:11.886 --> 00:25:13.346
And that's what you told Julie.

343
00:25:13.888 --> 00:25:16.265
I just thought that maybe if somehow
they brought some sort of ill--

344
00:25:16.349 --> 00:25:17.433
Okay. stop.

345
00:25:17.516 --> 00:25:19.018
The people hereâ€¦

346
00:25:20.228 --> 00:25:22.647
they're always one bad day away
from giving up.

347
00:25:23.189 --> 00:25:26.192
Giving up. losing hope.

348
00:25:26.275 --> 00:25:28.027
I know. it was-- It wasâ€¦

349
00:25:29.612 --> 00:25:30.655
I know.

350
00:25:33.824 --> 00:25:34.825
Look.

351
00:25:38.412 --> 00:25:41.540
We need to figure out
where you're going to live from now on.

352
00:25:41.624 --> 00:25:43.000
Where do you live?

353
00:25:44.293 --> 00:25:47.964
That big house up on the hill.
Colony House.

354
00:25:48.756 --> 00:25:50.132
There's plenty of room there.

355
00:25:51.092 --> 00:25:53.302
But there's so many people there.

356
00:25:54.595 --> 00:25:56.389
-Yeah.
-Can't I just stay at the clinic?

357
00:25:57.014 --> 00:26:00.142
Well. there's no extra rooms
in the clinic. soâ€¦

358
00:26:02.520 --> 00:26:03.813
Where does Sara live?

359
00:26:04.522 --> 00:26:05.982
What?

360
00:26:06.065 --> 00:26:07.650
She was really nice to me.

361
00:26:08.609 --> 00:26:10.361
That's not a good idea.

362
00:26:11.362 --> 00:26:14.407
Because ofâ€¦ of what she did?

363
00:26:17.660 --> 00:26:19.078
How did youâ€¦

364
00:26:20.121 --> 00:26:21.998
I'veâ€¦ I've heard people talking.

365
00:26:24.292 --> 00:26:26.627
Why would you want to live with her?

366
00:26:26.711 --> 00:26:29.463
Because I'veâ€¦
Because I've seen her kindness.

367
00:26:29.547 --> 00:26:32.258
And I don't think she's a bad person.

368
00:26:36.804 --> 00:26:39.348
You have no idea
the kind of person she is.

369
00:26:48.691 --> 00:26:50.901
I can't see you at all.
Are you okay?

370
00:26:52.570 --> 00:26:55.781
I'm fine.
Just letting my eyes adjust. that's all.

371
00:26:58.034 --> 00:27:00.286
How many of these books
am I looking for. anyway?

372
00:27:01.704 --> 00:27:04.457
He kept them all in a little blue bag.
They should be together.

373
00:27:04.540 --> 00:27:06.083
Little blue bag. huh?

374
00:27:07.001 --> 00:27:08.336
Piece of cake.

375
00:27:34.653 --> 00:27:35.946
Randall?

376
00:27:37.198 --> 00:27:38.407
I'm fine.

377
00:27:43.579 --> 00:27:44.914
What are we doing here?

378
00:27:47.750 --> 00:27:50.544
We got storage sheds around town.

379
00:27:51.170 --> 00:27:52.755
Storage room in the diner.

380
00:27:53.547 --> 00:27:55.674
They're filled with clothes. tools.

381
00:27:55.758 --> 00:27:57.510
everything we thought would be useful.

382
00:27:58.177 --> 00:28:00.554
This is everything else.

383
00:28:02.306 --> 00:28:03.557
Okay.

384
00:28:03.641 --> 00:28:05.976
I want you to treat this place
like a crime scene.

385
00:28:06.894 --> 00:28:11.774
Like. these things.
they tell a story. right?

386
00:28:11.857 --> 00:28:13.401
I want you to develop a narrative.

387
00:28:13.484 --> 00:28:15.194
Tell me everything there is to know

388
00:28:15.277 --> 00:28:17.071
about the people
this stuff belonged to.

389
00:28:17.154 --> 00:28:18.197
Why?

390
00:28:20.616 --> 00:28:21.992
Because I asked you to.

391
00:28:22.076 --> 00:28:23.452
So why don't you do it?

392
00:28:23.536 --> 00:28:24.495
You're a cop.

393
00:28:24.578 --> 00:28:26.997
You were trained to do this. I wasn't.

394
00:28:28.416 --> 00:28:30.751
There might be things we overlooked.

395
00:28:30.835 --> 00:28:32.837
something that'll help us get out of here.

396
00:28:33.671 --> 00:28:35.131
Tell me why we're really here.

397
00:28:35.214 --> 00:28:36.632
-I just did.
-Bullshit.

398
00:28:36.715 --> 00:28:37.716
Hey.

399
00:28:38.384 --> 00:28:40.261
You better tell me why we're really here.

400
00:28:46.392 --> 00:28:48.519
Because you remind me of someone.

401
00:28:49.812 --> 00:28:50.855
All right?

402
00:28:52.189 --> 00:28:53.607
You remind me

403
00:28:54.525 --> 00:28:58.195
of someone
I could have helped and I didn't.

404
00:29:00.990 --> 00:29:02.491
I don't get to get that back.

405
00:29:04.076 --> 00:29:05.744
But I'm not gonna stand here andâ€¦

406
00:29:07.288 --> 00:29:10.666
Look. I know you think
everything I said is bullshit.

407
00:29:10.749 --> 00:29:12.001
And maybe it is.

408
00:29:12.084 --> 00:29:14.211
Maybe it isn't. right?

409
00:29:14.295 --> 00:29:16.714
But if you do this for me.

410
00:29:16.797 --> 00:29:18.883
think about all the people
you might be helping.

411
00:29:18.966 --> 00:29:20.593
the people you might be saving.

412
00:29:20.676 --> 00:29:23.596
You think about the cop
who first put that badge on.

413
00:29:24.180 --> 00:29:26.599
You do all that
and you still want that bulletâ€¦

414
00:29:27.892 --> 00:29:29.477
then yeah. we'll talk.

415
00:29:30.311 --> 00:29:31.437
It's a promise.

416
00:29:55.211 --> 00:29:56.295
Donna?

417
00:30:22.154 --> 00:30:24.448
I think she went back to town.

418
00:30:25.991 --> 00:30:27.326
You need something?

419
00:30:29.828 --> 00:30:31.497
No. I'm okay.

420
00:30:31.997 --> 00:30:33.374
Are you?

421
00:30:34.208 --> 00:30:37.670
Forty years. I sat in my house
after my family disappeared.

422
00:30:37.753 --> 00:30:39.880
I was a lot of things.

423
00:30:40.506 --> 00:30:42.967
"Okay" was never one of them.

424
00:30:44.552 --> 00:30:46.554
-I should go home.
-Where are you headed?

425
00:30:47.805 --> 00:30:49.056
Just going home.

426
00:30:50.558 --> 00:30:51.767
Well. I'll walk with you.

427
00:30:51.850 --> 00:30:54.186
Henry. no. It's okay.
I can go by myself.

428
00:30:54.270 --> 00:30:56.981
But. Tabitha. I don't think
you should be alone right now.

429
00:31:00.150 --> 00:31:02.820
So where are you really going?

430
00:31:03.696 --> 00:31:05.072
I'm going home.

431
00:31:05.155 --> 00:31:06.949
And where are you going after that?

432
00:31:07.491 --> 00:31:09.702
Henry. I don't know
what you're talking about.

433
00:31:09.785 --> 00:31:12.329
Sure you do.
You're good at a lot of things. Tabitha.

434
00:31:12.413 --> 00:31:14.206
Lying is definitely not among them.

435
00:31:14.290 --> 00:31:17.334
So we can play the whole charade
of me dropping you off

436
00:31:17.418 --> 00:31:19.670
at your house and then waiting
to see where else you go.

437
00:31:19.753 --> 00:31:21.839
Okay. I'm going to find
the lighthouse. okay?

438
00:31:24.425 --> 00:31:26.218
I'm gonna find my way back
to the lighthouse.

439
00:31:27.636 --> 00:31:28.971
I got out of here once.

440
00:31:30.639 --> 00:31:32.641
If I find the lighthouse. maybe. maybe.

441
00:31:32.725 --> 00:31:35.269
hopefully I can do it again
and take my children with me.

442
00:31:36.061 --> 00:31:37.354
I'm not gonna let them die here.

443
00:31:37.438 --> 00:31:39.607
How? Donna said no one knows
where the lighthouse is.

444
00:31:39.690 --> 00:31:40.691
No. they don't.

445
00:31:40.774 --> 00:31:43.068
That's why I have to do it again.
like I did the last time.

446
00:31:43.152 --> 00:31:44.737
I have to go through The Bottle Tree

447
00:31:45.237 --> 00:31:47.948
The man in the pool. Dale. right?

448
00:31:48.032 --> 00:31:50.159
He died when he tried going through.

449
00:31:50.242 --> 00:31:52.369
Yeah. butâ€¦ Okay. what if it wasâ€¦

450
00:31:52.953 --> 00:31:55.873
What if it was not meant for him?
What if it was only meant for me?

451
00:31:55.956 --> 00:31:57.041
And what if you're wrong?

452
00:31:57.124 --> 00:32:00.544
What if you end up stuck in the side
of God-knows-what. somewhere...

453
00:32:00.628 --> 00:32:02.463
Well. I don't know. I don't know. Henry.

454
00:32:02.546 --> 00:32:03.839
I have to try.

455
00:32:03.922 --> 00:32:04.965
Okay.

456
00:32:05.841 --> 00:32:07.426
-I'm coming with you.
-No. Henry.

457
00:32:07.509 --> 00:32:09.678
You said you're going
to The Bottle Tree. right?

458
00:32:09.762 --> 00:32:13.474
I want to see it. I want to see
the tree my wife died trying to reach.

459
00:32:18.312 --> 00:32:19.605
Henry. I have to tell you something.

460
00:32:19.688 --> 00:32:21.106
She was my wife.

461
00:32:21.815 --> 00:32:22.858
Please.

462
00:32:26.862 --> 00:32:28.822
Okay. Let's go.

463
00:32:28.906 --> 00:32:30.157
-Okay.
-Yeah.

464
00:32:35.954 --> 00:32:37.539
Where are we going?

465
00:32:37.623 --> 00:32:39.166
Just a little further.

466
00:32:41.877 --> 00:32:43.671
Why won't you tell me what's in the bag?

467
00:32:44.421 --> 00:32:45.422
You'll see.

468
00:32:54.515 --> 00:32:55.974
Ever heard of a rage room?

469
00:32:56.600 --> 00:32:58.268
They're really popular in Japan.

470
00:32:59.770 --> 00:33:01.772
Sort of a way to lash out.

471
00:33:02.856 --> 00:33:06.985
You know. let go without hurting somebody
or breaking shit that you need.

472
00:33:14.118 --> 00:33:15.786
Ellis. this is really sweet.

473
00:33:15.869 --> 00:33:17.496
but I don't know
how this is going to help.

474
00:33:17.579 --> 00:33:21.375
When my mom died.
you were the one that brought me back.

475
00:33:23.919 --> 00:33:25.546
You didn't even know me very well.

476
00:33:26.088 --> 00:33:30.092
But you knew that I was still in there.
underneath all theâ€¦

477
00:33:31.677 --> 00:33:34.680
the dark. horrible shit
that I was going through.

478
00:33:34.763 --> 00:33:36.557
And you never gave up on me.

479
00:33:37.349 --> 00:33:39.268
Not until you finally pulled me out.

480
00:33:40.352 --> 00:33:41.603
It's my turn now.

481
00:33:42.312 --> 00:33:43.564
Give it a shot.

482
00:33:46.358 --> 00:33:47.359
Soâ€¦

483
00:33:48.527 --> 00:33:49.778
you want the crowbar?

484
00:33:52.364 --> 00:33:53.490
Or the bat?

485
00:34:05.377 --> 00:34:06.795
Definitely the bat.

486
00:34:08.213 --> 00:34:09.465
That's my girl.

487
00:34:26.106 --> 00:34:27.232
It's all yours.

488
00:34:57.930 --> 00:34:59.932
Okay. so let me get this straight.

489
00:35:00.557 --> 00:35:05.604
You made up this Lake of Tears
as part of a game

490
00:35:05.687 --> 00:35:08.941
that you used to play with finger puppets.

491
00:35:09.024 --> 00:35:10.400
It wasn't a game.

492
00:35:10.943 --> 00:35:12.277
It was a story.

493
00:35:12.361 --> 00:35:17.032
Okay. so you told a story about this lake.
some finger puppets. and nowâ€¦

494
00:35:18.075 --> 00:35:20.994
Now what? You think the lake is here
because your dad told you

495
00:35:21.078 --> 00:35:22.371
that you need to find it?

496
00:35:24.081 --> 00:35:25.874
Maybe I didn't make it up.

497
00:35:27.125 --> 00:35:28.544
Maybe I just thought I did.

498
00:35:31.296 --> 00:35:32.381
I'm confused.

499
00:35:33.882 --> 00:35:35.926
Do you remember the red rocks
we found at the settlement?

500
00:35:36.009 --> 00:35:38.762
-Yeah.
-My mom thought she made them up

501
00:35:38.846 --> 00:35:41.098
because she used to have
nightmares about them.

502
00:35:41.181 --> 00:35:44.935
But the reason she saw those rocks
was because they were here.

503
00:35:45.435 --> 00:35:47.312
Maybe it's the same with the lake.

504
00:35:48.897 --> 00:35:50.899
Maybe I used it in my storyâ€¦

505
00:35:52.985 --> 00:35:55.779
because it's real and I just didn't know.

506
00:35:59.032 --> 00:36:01.034
What were you doing at The Brundles?

507
00:36:01.118 --> 00:36:02.828
It's an old meditation technique.

508
00:36:04.079 --> 00:36:05.497
Why were you meditating?

509
00:36:06.039 --> 00:36:07.457
Because Iâ€¦

510
00:36:09.710 --> 00:36:10.836
I'm trying to remember something.

511
00:36:10.919 --> 00:36:12.963
I'm trying remember something
that I used to know.

512
00:36:15.007 --> 00:36:16.675
Something that'll help us leave.

513
00:36:19.261 --> 00:36:22.055
So we're both looking for something
that can help everyone.

514
00:36:23.348 --> 00:36:24.683
Yeah. I guess we are.

515
00:36:26.268 --> 00:36:28.228
Hey. Victor. we got a lake to find.

516
00:36:33.400 --> 00:36:34.401
Victor?

517
00:36:36.153 --> 00:36:37.237
Hey.

518
00:36:41.950 --> 00:36:43.076
What is that?

519
00:36:46.872 --> 00:36:47.915
Victor.

520
00:36:54.880 --> 00:36:56.048
Victor!

521
00:36:56.131 --> 00:36:57.341
Victor! Come on.

522
00:36:59.134 --> 00:37:00.636
-Victor!
-Victor!

523
